WEBVTT

00:00:01.772 --> 00:00:03.983 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, now we’re looking forward to hearing

00:00:03.983 --> 00:00:07.611 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from a graduate of the 41st class of Gilead,

00:00:07.611 --> 00:00:11.198 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
a member of the Governing Body,
Brother Gerrit Lösch.

00:00:11.198 --> 00:00:15.119 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brother Lösch has just completed 25 years

00:00:15.119 --> 00:00:17.454 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of service as a member of the Governing Body.

00:00:17.454 --> 00:00:19.456 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How wonderful!

00:00:24.837 --> 00:00:29.258 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brother Lösch will speak to us now
on the subject “Are You Ready?”

00:00:32.845 --> 00:00:35.139 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Are you ready?

00:00:35.139 --> 00:00:38.100 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
As Gilead students,
no doubt you have been asked

00:00:38.100 --> 00:00:41.854 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that question many times this week.

00:00:41.854 --> 00:00:45.232 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Boy Scouts
have the greeting,

00:00:45.232 --> 00:00:48.068 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘Always Prepared.’

00:00:48.068 --> 00:00:50.362 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What are they prepared for?

00:00:50.362 --> 00:00:52.865 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They’re supposed to be ready, or prepared,

00:00:52.865 --> 00:00:57.328 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for doing at least one good deed each day.

00:00:57.328 --> 00:01:02.333 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
True Christians are also
supposed to be always prepared.

00:01:02.333 --> 00:01:04.418 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Prepared for what?

00:01:04.418 --> 00:01:07.546 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Yes, for doing good deeds and also prepared

00:01:07.546 --> 00:01:11.592 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for the final return of the Lord Jesus

00:01:11.592 --> 00:01:16.055 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
as a mighty heavenly King
in the great tribulation.

00:01:16.055 --> 00:01:21.060 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jesus began to rule
over his congregation, when?

00:01:21.060 --> 00:01:24.730 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, I’m sure you understand,

00:01:24.730 --> 00:01:28.400 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
at Pentecost 33 of our Common Era,

00:01:28.400 --> 00:01:31.236 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
over his congregation.

00:01:31.236 --> 00:01:36.241 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The <i>Insight </i>book says:
“The Scriptures show [and this is a quote]

00:01:36.241 --> 00:01:40.913 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“that from Pentecost 33 C.E. onward,

00:01:40.913 --> 00:01:43.624 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“a spiritual kingdom

00:01:43.624 --> 00:01:47.419 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
was set up over his disciples.”

00:01:47.419 --> 00:01:51.924 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Paul reminded Christians of Colossae:

00:01:51.924 --> 00:01:55.135 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“He rescued us
from the authority of the darkness

00:01:55.135 --> 00:01:58.263 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and transferred us into the kingdom

00:01:58.263 --> 00:02:02.643 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of his beloved Son.”—Colossians 1:13.

00:02:04.645 --> 00:02:08.565 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jesus has been ruling
as King over his disciples

00:02:08.565 --> 00:02:11.944 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
ever since Pentecost 33 C.E.

00:02:11.944 --> 00:02:15.572 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He’s always been
the head of the congregation,

00:02:15.572 --> 00:02:17.658 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
which is compared to a body.

00:02:17.658 --> 00:02:22.663 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So he ruled as King
during the Middle Ages also.

00:02:22.663 --> 00:02:26.500 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
However, something changed in 1914 C.E.

00:02:26.500 --> 00:02:28.544 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What was it?

00:02:28.544 --> 00:02:30.671 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, from that time onward,

00:02:30.671 --> 00:02:34.174 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jesus would rule also over his enemies,

00:02:34.174 --> 00:02:36.385 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
both in heaven and on earth.

00:02:36.385 --> 00:02:39.179 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The prophecy was fulfilled

00:02:39.179 --> 00:02:43.642 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that we find in Psalm 110.

00:02:43.642 --> 00:02:48.022 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And there it says in Psalm 110:

00:02:53.110 --> 00:02:56.238 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Jehovah declared to my Lord:

00:02:56.238 --> 00:02:59.366 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘Sit at my right hand until I place

00:02:59.366 --> 00:03:02.578 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“your enemies as a stool for your feet.’

00:03:02.578 --> 00:03:04.913 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Jehovah will extend the scepter

00:03:04.913 --> 00:03:08.042 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“of your power out of Zion, saying:

00:03:08.042 --> 00:03:12.588 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘Go subduing in the midst of your enemies.’”

00:03:12.588 --> 00:03:16.091 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, we understand that in 1914

00:03:16.091 --> 00:03:19.928 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he returned as heavenly King to rule.

00:03:19.928 --> 00:03:22.514 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Since that time, many things are happening

00:03:22.514 --> 00:03:26.143 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
showing us that he’s actually
‘ruling in the midst of his enemies.’

00:03:26.143 --> 00:03:30.397 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He’s not ruling only over his congregation.

00:03:30.397 --> 00:03:34.026 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Satan and his agents were not able to prevent

00:03:34.026 --> 00:03:38.322 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the appointment
of “the faithful and discreet slave.”

00:03:38.322 --> 00:03:42.826 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But what about Jesus’ final coming as Judge?

00:03:42.826 --> 00:03:46.580 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When will that return happen?

00:03:46.580 --> 00:03:50.334 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, we don’t know exactly,
but Jesus predicted events

00:03:50.334 --> 00:03:54.755 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from which we can conclude
when it would be close.

00:03:54.755 --> 00:03:57.466 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Although Jesus said that we would not be able

00:03:57.466 --> 00:04:00.928 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to know in advance the exact time or date,

00:04:00.928 --> 00:04:03.639 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he prophesied events that would occur

00:04:03.639 --> 00:04:06.683 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from which we
could notice the nearness

00:04:06.683 --> 00:04:10.813 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of his final coming as Judge.

00:04:10.813 --> 00:04:15.734 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In the past, many people
attempted to pinpoint his return.

00:04:15.734 --> 00:04:19.488 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
By their expectations and predictions,

00:04:19.488 --> 00:04:23.784 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
they aroused curiosity,

00:04:23.784 --> 00:04:27.746 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but many times these predictions failed.

00:04:27.746 --> 00:04:29.832 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Even in the first century,

00:04:29.832 --> 00:04:33.710 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
there already existed
among Christians

00:04:33.710 --> 00:04:35.754 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
false expectations.

00:04:35.754 --> 00:04:38.423 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Thessalonians, for instance, had such.

00:04:38.423 --> 00:04:43.137 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Paul needed to write to them
for them to find balance.

00:04:43.137 --> 00:04:48.851 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Second Thessalonians 2:1

00:04:48.851 --> 00:04:51.145 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
onward says:

00:04:51.145 --> 00:04:53.897 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“However, brothers, concerning the presence

00:04:53.897 --> 00:04:58.277 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“of our Lord Jesus Christ
and our being gathered together to him,

00:04:58.277 --> 00:05:00.737 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“we ask you not to be quickly shaken

00:05:00.737 --> 00:05:03.407 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“from your reason nor to be alarmed

00:05:03.407 --> 00:05:07.369 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“either by an inspired statement
or by a spoken message

00:05:07.369 --> 00:05:10.622 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“or by a letter appearing to be from us,

00:05:10.622 --> 00:05:15.586 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“to the effect
that the day of Jehovah is here.

00:05:15.586 --> 00:05:19.631 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let no one lead you astray,”

00:05:19.631 --> 00:05:22.050 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he says in verse 3.

00:05:22.050 --> 00:05:26.638 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There were many other false expectations

00:05:26.638 --> 00:05:30.309 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
during the centuries that followed.

00:05:30.309 --> 00:05:34.688 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Martin of Tours, a French bishop,

00:05:34.688 --> 00:05:39.234 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
stated that the world
would end before the year 400.

00:05:39.234 --> 00:05:42.529 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Hippolytus and two others predicted Jesus

00:05:42.529 --> 00:05:45.657 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to return in the year 500

00:05:45.657 --> 00:05:48.577 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of our time.

00:05:48.577 --> 00:05:52.539 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Africanus, Sextus Julius

00:05:52.539 --> 00:05:55.375 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
(with his Latin name),

00:05:55.375 --> 00:05:58.545 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
predicted it for the year 800.

00:05:58.545 --> 00:06:02.341 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Of course, also the year 1000 was predicted,

00:06:02.341 --> 00:06:05.761 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
including by a pope, Pope Sylvester,

00:06:05.761 --> 00:06:08.222 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
as some sources claim.

00:06:08.222 --> 00:06:13.185 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Pope Innocent III predicted the end

00:06:13.185 --> 00:06:17.439 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for the year 1284,

00:06:17.439 --> 00:06:22.444 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
which would have been
666 years after the rise of Islam.

00:06:24.488 --> 00:06:27.532 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Famous painter Sandro Botticelli

00:06:27.532 --> 00:06:31.954 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
predicted the year 1504.

00:06:33.163 --> 00:06:38.085 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Astrologers in London
predicted February 1, 1524.

00:06:38.085 --> 00:06:43.090 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
As a result, 20,000 Londoners
left their homes for higher ground.

00:06:44.883 --> 00:06:48.762 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In 1533, Melchior Hofmann predicted

00:06:48.762 --> 00:06:53.141 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Christ’s second coming
to take place that year in Strasbourg.

00:06:53.141 --> 00:06:57.187 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He claimed that 144,000
people would be saved,

00:06:57.187 --> 00:07:01.441 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
while the rest of the world
would be consumed by fire.

00:07:01.441 --> 00:07:05.988 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Luther, a German priest
and professor of theology,

00:07:05.988 --> 00:07:08.407 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
predicted the end of the world would occur 

00:07:08.407 --> 00:07:12.369 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
no later than the year 1600.

00:07:12.369 --> 00:07:16.123 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Christopher Columbus predicted

00:07:16.123 --> 00:07:19.251 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
(famous, we all know him)

00:07:19.251 --> 00:07:24.256 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in 1501 in his <i>Book of Prophecies</i>

00:07:24.256 --> 00:07:28.677 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that the world would end in 1656.

00:07:30.387 --> 00:07:33.682 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
John Napier predicted

00:07:33.682 --> 00:07:37.978 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the end of the world for 1700.

00:07:37.978 --> 00:07:41.023 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Christopher Love, a Presbyterian minister,

00:07:41.023 --> 00:07:44.526 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
predicted the year 1805.

00:07:44.526 --> 00:07:47.237 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
A Lutheran clergyman,

00:07:47.237 --> 00:07:49.448 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Johann Albrecht Bengel,

00:07:49.448 --> 00:07:52.534 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
predicted the year 1836.

00:07:52.534 --> 00:07:55.287 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And the founder of the Methodist church,

00:07:55.287 --> 00:07:59.958 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
John Wesley, predicted the same year, 1836.

00:07:59.958 --> 00:08:02.753 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Miller, a Baptist preacher,

00:08:02.753 --> 00:08:07.132 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
predicted the date March 21, 1844,

00:08:07.132 --> 00:08:09.509 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for the return of Christ,

00:08:09.509 --> 00:08:13.347 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but later he revised it to October 22.

00:08:13.347 --> 00:08:17.100 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Adventist preacher Wendell

00:08:17.100 --> 00:08:20.854 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
predicted the year 1873.

00:08:20.854 --> 00:08:25.567 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When Jesus did not come,
he reinterpreted his prediction,

00:08:25.567 --> 00:08:28.362 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
saying that Jesus
had returned indeed,

00:08:28.362 --> 00:08:31.031 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but in invisible form.

00:08:31.031 --> 00:08:34.826 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Our brothers expected the return of Christ

00:08:34.826 --> 00:08:37.996 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
first for 1874

00:08:37.996 --> 00:08:40.665 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and then for 1914.

00:08:40.665 --> 00:08:43.710 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They also initially expected

00:08:43.710 --> 00:08:46.755 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
his return to be visible

00:08:46.755 --> 00:08:51.760 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but then understood
that it would be invisible.

00:08:51.760 --> 00:08:56.098 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They also expected
the glorification of the “little flock”

00:08:56.098 --> 00:08:59.559 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for the spring of 1918.

00:08:59.559 --> 00:09:04.022 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The year when Brother Russell died, 1916,

00:09:04.022 --> 00:09:08.151 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the brothers entered
a period of serious testing.

00:09:08.151 --> 00:09:10.445 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Some even left the truth.

00:09:10.445 --> 00:09:15.450 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In 1919, faithful ones consolidated again.

00:09:15.450 --> 00:09:18.495 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
A hundred years have passed,

00:09:18.495 --> 00:09:23.500 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
1919 to now 2019, a hundred years.

00:09:23.500 --> 00:09:28.505 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Will special prophecies
be fulfilled a hundred years after 1919?

00:09:28.505 --> 00:09:32.676 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, this is just a question.

00:09:32.676 --> 00:09:36.012 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
No answer.

00:09:36.012 --> 00:09:38.890 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There were serious testings

00:09:38.890 --> 00:09:42.394 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
during the year 1925 also.

00:09:42.394 --> 00:09:47.065 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And for that year,
our brothers had great expectations.

00:09:48.859 --> 00:09:51.194 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It said in one of our publications:

00:09:51.194 --> 00:09:53.405 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“We may confidently expect

00:09:53.405 --> 00:09:57.409 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“[that’s from the booklet
<i>Millions Now Living Will Never Die</i>]

00:09:59.494 --> 00:10:03.415 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“that 1925 will mark

00:10:03.415 --> 00:10:05.876 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“the return [from the dead]

00:10:05.876 --> 00:10:10.130 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“of Abraham, Isaac, Jacob,
and the faithful prophets of old . . .

00:10:10.130 --> 00:10:13.758 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to the condition of human perfection.”

00:10:13.758 --> 00:10:15.886 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Not only was the resurrection

00:10:15.886 --> 00:10:19.514 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of faithful men of old expected in 1925

00:10:19.514 --> 00:10:22.267 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but some hoped that anointed Christians

00:10:22.267 --> 00:10:25.812 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
might receive
their heavenly reward in that year.

00:10:28.440 --> 00:10:32.152 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
From the <i>1987 Yearbook</i>, we learned:

00:10:32.152 --> 00:10:36.656 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“The year 1925 started very promisingly

00:10:36.656 --> 00:10:41.661 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“with the new Bethel home
and factory in Bern [Switzerland]. . . .

00:10:41.661 --> 00:10:45.123 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“However, some had
their [own] personal convictions

00:10:45.123 --> 00:10:48.168 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“with respect to the year 1925.

00:10:48.168 --> 00:10:50.587 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Would they let themselves be admonished

00:10:50.587 --> 00:10:55.592 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“by <i>The Watch Tower </i>of January 1, 1925?

00:10:55.592 --> 00:10:59.054 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“[<i>The Watch Tower</i>] cautioned
[and I quote]:

00:10:59.054 --> 00:11:01.723 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘The year 1925 is here.

00:11:01.723 --> 00:11:05.894 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘With great expectation
Christians have looked forward to this year.

00:11:05.894 --> 00:11:10.232 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘Many have confidently expected
that all members of the body of Christ

00:11:10.232 --> 00:11:13.693 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘will be changed
to heavenly glory during the year.

00:11:13.693 --> 00:11:15.904 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘This may be accomplished.

00:11:15.904 --> 00:11:18.073 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘It may not be.

00:11:18.073 --> 00:11:20.992 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘In his own due time God will accomplish

00:11:20.992 --> 00:11:23.828 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘his purposes concerning his own people.

00:11:23.828 --> 00:11:26.998 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘Christians should not be
so deeply concerned

00:11:26.998 --> 00:11:30.210 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘about what may <i>transpire </i>during this year

00:11:30.210 --> 00:11:34.881 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that they would fail to joyfully <i>do</i>
what the Lord would have them to do.’

00:11:36.758 --> 00:11:39.761 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Among others, Jakob Weber,

00:11:39.761 --> 00:11:43.181 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“who was responsible
for the [field] Service Desk

00:11:43.181 --> 00:11:46.309 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“at Bethel [branch in Switzerland] . . . ,

00:11:46.309 --> 00:11:48.812 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“was so sure that all the anointed

00:11:48.812 --> 00:11:52.232 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“would be glorified in heaven
by the end of the year

00:11:52.232 --> 00:11:54.651 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“[1925]

00:11:54.651 --> 00:11:58.530 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“that he pursued a ‘liquidation course.’

00:11:58.530 --> 00:12:02.534 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“He sent large quantities of literature

00:12:02.534 --> 00:12:07.539 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“to congregations
without having received orders for it,

00:12:07.539 --> 00:12:10.667 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“instructing them
to distribute the publications

00:12:10.667 --> 00:12:13.086 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“free of charge in their territory

00:12:13.086 --> 00:12:16.715 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“before the end of 1925.

00:12:16.715 --> 00:12:21.595 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“All the efforts of the brothers at Bethel
to reason with him were to no avail.

00:12:21.595 --> 00:12:25.849 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Finally, he left not only Bethel
but [even] the truth

00:12:25.849 --> 00:12:28.643 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and caused much grief among the brothers

00:12:28.643 --> 00:12:33.023 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“throughout the country [Switzerland],
since he drew many with him.

00:12:33.023 --> 00:12:37.986 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Some congregations were reduced
to less than half their former size.”

00:12:40.113 --> 00:12:44.326 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What about expectations
for the year 50 years later

00:12:44.326 --> 00:12:47.537 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—1925-1975?

00:12:49.956 --> 00:12:54.169 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In <i>The Watchtower, </i>March 15, 1980,

00:12:54.169 --> 00:12:57.547 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
a comment is made, and it says:

00:12:57.547 --> 00:13:01.009 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“In modern times such eagerness,
commendable in itself,

00:13:01.009 --> 00:13:03.595 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“has led to attempts at setting dates

00:13:03.595 --> 00:13:07.140 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“for the desired liberation
from the suffering and troubles

00:13:07.140 --> 00:13:11.561 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“that are the lot
of persons throughout the earth.

00:13:11.561 --> 00:13:13.647 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“With the appearance of the book

00:13:13.647 --> 00:13:17.067 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
<i>“Life Everlasting</i>
<i>—in Freedom of the Sons of God,</i>

00:13:17.067 --> 00:13:19.694 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and its comments
as to how appropriate it would be

00:13:19.694 --> 00:13:21.696 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“for the millennial reign of Christ

00:13:21.696 --> 00:13:25.909 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“to parallel the seventh millennium
of man’s existence,

00:13:25.909 --> 00:13:28.620 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“considerable expectation was aroused

00:13:28.620 --> 00:13:31.498 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“regarding the year 1975.

00:13:31.498 --> 00:13:34.793 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“There were statements
made then, and thereafter,

00:13:34.793 --> 00:13:39.172 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“stressing that this was only a possibility.

00:13:39.172 --> 00:13:43.301 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Unfortunately, however
[says <i>The Watchtower</i>],

00:13:43.301 --> 00:13:46.262 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“along with such cautionary information,

00:13:46.262 --> 00:13:48.556 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“there were other statements published

00:13:48.556 --> 00:13:52.102 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“that implied that such realization

00:13:52.102 --> 00:13:56.940 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“of hopes by that year [1975]

00:13:56.940 --> 00:14:01.611 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“was more of a probability
than a mere possibility.

00:14:01.611 --> 00:14:05.865 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“It is to be regretted
[admits <i>The Watchtower</i>]

00:14:05.865 --> 00:14:08.827 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“that these latter statements

00:14:08.827 --> 00:14:12.330 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“apparently overshadowed the cautionary ones

00:14:12.330 --> 00:14:14.374 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and contributed to a buildup

00:14:14.374 --> 00:14:18.002 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“of the expectation already initiated.

00:14:19.963 --> 00:14:24.592 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“In its issue of July 15, 1976, 

00:14:24.592 --> 00:14:27.345 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
<i>“The Watchtower, </i>
commenting on the inadvisability

00:14:27.345 --> 00:14:31.474 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“of setting our sights
on a certain date, stated:

00:14:31.474 --> 00:14:35.854 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘If anyone has been disappointed
through not following this line of thought,

00:14:35.854 --> 00:14:39.274 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘he should now concentrate
on adjusting his viewpoint,

00:14:39.274 --> 00:14:44.154 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘seeing that it was not
the word of God that failed

00:14:44.154 --> 00:14:47.198 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘or deceived him and brought disappointment,

00:14:47.198 --> 00:14:51.369 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“but that his own understanding
was based on wrong premises.’

00:14:51.369 --> 00:14:54.289 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“In saying ‘anyone,’ <i>The Watchtower </i>

00:14:54.289 --> 00:14:58.752 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“included all disappointed ones
of Jehovah’s Witnesses,

00:14:58.752 --> 00:15:01.755 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“hence including <i>persons having to do</i>

00:15:01.755 --> 00:15:05.133 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
<i>“with</i><i> </i><i>the publication of the information </i>

00:15:05.133 --> 00:15:07.385 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“that contributed to the buildup

00:15:07.385 --> 00:15:12.140 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of hopes centered on that date.”
(end of quote)

00:15:12.140 --> 00:15:15.393 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So, very humbly, <i>The Watchtower</i>

00:15:15.393 --> 00:15:19.856 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
admitted that on July 15, 1976.

00:15:19.856 --> 00:15:22.108 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Nevertheless, there is no reason for us

00:15:22.108 --> 00:15:25.445 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“to be shaken in faith in God’s promises.

00:15:25.445 --> 00:15:28.198 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Rather, as a consequence, we are all moved

00:15:28.198 --> 00:15:30.700 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“to make a closer examination

00:15:30.700 --> 00:15:34.996 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“of the Scriptures
regarding this matter of a day of judgment.

00:15:34.996 --> 00:15:39.918 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“In doing so, we find
that the important thing is not the date.

00:15:39.918 --> 00:15:43.421 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“What is important
is our keeping ever in mind

00:15:43.421 --> 00:15:45.965 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“that <i>there is such a day</i>

00:15:45.965 --> 00:15:48.343 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“—and it is getting closer
and it will require

00:15:48.343 --> 00:15:51.054 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“an accounting on the part of all of us.

00:15:51.054 --> 00:15:53.097 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Peter said that Christians

00:15:53.097 --> 00:15:56.559 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“should rightly be
‘awaiting and keeping close in mind

00:15:56.559 --> 00:15:59.562 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the presence of the day of Jehovah.’”

00:15:59.562 --> 00:16:03.650 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There’s good reason to remain in expectation

00:16:03.650 --> 00:16:06.277 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—Jesus told us to do so!

00:16:06.277 --> 00:16:10.406 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In this regard,
Jehovah’s organization has set an example.

00:16:10.406 --> 00:16:14.536 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Although sometimes
promoting wrong expectations,

00:16:14.536 --> 00:16:17.914 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
our publications
have consistently exhorted us

00:16:17.914 --> 00:16:22.710 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to “await and keep close in mind
the presence of the day of Jehovah”

00:16:22.710 --> 00:16:27.715 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and to fix our hope
on God’s promised new world.

00:16:27.715 --> 00:16:30.969 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Since keeping in expectation was appropriate

00:16:30.969 --> 00:16:33.972 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for Christians living centuries ago,

00:16:33.972 --> 00:16:36.432 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
it is particularly important for us.

00:16:36.432 --> 00:16:38.017 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Why?

00:16:38.017 --> 00:16:40.770 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Because we are living
during Christ’s presence.

00:16:40.770 --> 00:16:45.441 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The sign of his presence
has been in evidence since 1914.

00:16:45.441 --> 00:16:47.652 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And the multifeatured sign,

00:16:47.652 --> 00:16:52.615 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
which includes worsening world conditions
and global Kingdom preaching,

00:16:52.615 --> 00:16:57.078 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is proof that we are living
in “the conclusion of the system of things.”

00:16:57.078 --> 00:16:59.122 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Since Jesus did not say

00:16:59.122 --> 00:17:03.751 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
how long that period
of time would go, or go on,

00:17:03.751 --> 00:17:06.296 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
before the final end arrives,

00:17:06.296 --> 00:17:10.592 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we need to be especially vigilant, watchful.

00:17:10.592 --> 00:17:14.470 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There’s no doubt
that world conditions are deteriorating.

00:17:14.470 --> 00:17:19.475 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But how bad do you expect conditions
to become before the great tribulation?

00:17:19.475 --> 00:17:21.936 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jesus said that most people

00:17:21.936 --> 00:17:24.981 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
would take “no note” of his presence,

00:17:24.981 --> 00:17:28.234 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
carrying on with life’s normal activities

00:17:28.234 --> 00:17:30.695 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
until it is too late.

00:17:30.695 --> 00:17:35.325 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Thus, the Scriptures indicate
that world conditions during the last days

00:17:35.325 --> 00:17:37.744 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
would not become so extreme

00:17:37.744 --> 00:17:42.624 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that people would be forced
to believe that the end is near.

00:17:43.666 --> 00:17:48.671 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
On the other hand,
for the composite sign to serve its purpose,

00:17:48.671 --> 00:17:52.592 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the fulfillment of it
would have to be obvious enough

00:17:52.592 --> 00:17:55.178 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to command the attention of those

00:17:55.178 --> 00:17:57.889 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who have been obeying Jesus’ counsel

00:17:57.889 --> 00:18:00.141 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to “keep on the watch.”

00:18:00.141 --> 00:18:03.603 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And that has been the case since 1914.

00:18:03.603 --> 00:18:07.231 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
From that time onward,
the features of the sign

00:18:07.231 --> 00:18:09.525 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
have been undergoing fulfillment.

00:18:09.525 --> 00:18:13.446 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Clearly, we are now living in the time

00:18:13.446 --> 00:18:17.450 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of “the conclusion of the system of things.”

00:18:17.450 --> 00:18:20.119 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Why, then, should Christians today keep

00:18:20.119 --> 00:18:23.581 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in orientation or expectation?

00:18:23.581 --> 00:18:27.126 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Out of obedience to Jesus Christ,

00:18:27.126 --> 00:18:29.837 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
out of love for him,

00:18:29.837 --> 00:18:33.925 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
out of faith in his promises,

00:18:33.925 --> 00:18:38.012 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we recognize the sign of his presence.

00:18:38.012 --> 00:18:40.223 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Our expectations are based,

00:18:40.223 --> 00:18:44.644 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
not on a naive readiness to believe anything,

00:18:44.644 --> 00:18:48.606 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but on solid Scriptural evidence
that compels us

00:18:48.606 --> 00:18:52.402 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to remain vigilant, awake, watchful and, yes,

00:18:52.402 --> 00:18:56.197 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in expectation of the end
of this wicked system.

00:18:57.824 --> 00:19:02.412 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Many of us have been keeping awake
spiritually already for decades.

00:19:02.412 --> 00:19:06.874 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
However, let us not allow the passing of time

00:19:06.874 --> 00:19:11.546 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to weaken our resolve to keep in expectation.

00:19:11.546 --> 00:19:14.674 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We need to be ready for Jesus’ arrival

00:19:14.674 --> 00:19:19.095 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
as Executioner to end this system of things.

00:19:19.095 --> 00:19:22.473 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Remember that Jesus exhorted his followers

00:19:22.473 --> 00:19:24.767 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in accord with the prophecy

00:19:24.767 --> 00:19:28.855 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in Mark chapter 13, starting with verse 33:

00:19:28.855 --> 00:19:31.816 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Keep looking, keep awake,

00:19:31.816 --> 00:19:34.652 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“for you do not know
when the appointed time is.

00:19:34.652 --> 00:19:36.654 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“It is like a man traveling abroad

00:19:36.654 --> 00:19:38.698 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“who left his house and gave the authority

00:19:38.698 --> 00:19:41.409 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“to his slaves, to each one his work,

00:19:41.409 --> 00:19:44.287 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and commanded the doorkeeper
to keep on the watch.

00:19:44.287 --> 00:19:46.372 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Keep on the watch, therefore,

00:19:46.372 --> 00:19:49.667 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“for you do not know
when the master of the house is coming,

00:19:49.667 --> 00:19:52.962 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“whether late in the day or at midnight

00:19:52.962 --> 00:19:56.340 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“or before dawn or early in the morning,

00:19:56.340 --> 00:19:58.718 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“in order that when he comes suddenly,

00:19:58.718 --> 00:20:00.887 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“he does not find you sleeping.

00:20:00.887 --> 00:20:04.724 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But what I say to you, I say to all:
Keep on the watch.”

00:20:06.309 --> 00:20:09.228 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Upon recognizing
that Christ’s presence

00:20:09.228 --> 00:20:11.606 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
began in 1914,

00:20:11.606 --> 00:20:13.983 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jesus’ followers rightly prepared

00:20:13.983 --> 00:20:17.487 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for a possible early arrival of the end.

00:20:17.487 --> 00:20:21.115 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They did so by intensifying
their Kingdom-preaching work.

00:20:21.115 --> 00:20:24.619 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jesus indicated that he might come later

00:20:24.619 --> 00:20:27.497 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—at “dawn or early in the morning,” he said.

00:20:27.497 --> 00:20:31.417 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
If that happened,
how were his followers to respond?

00:20:31.417 --> 00:20:34.629 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He said: “<i>Keep </i>on the watch.”

00:20:34.629 --> 00:20:39.509 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So a long wait
would not justify mentally postponing the end

00:20:39.509 --> 00:20:43.012 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or totally dismissing their expectations.

00:20:43.012 --> 00:20:46.265 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Consider the prophet Habakkuk,

00:20:46.265 --> 00:20:50.770 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who was commissioned to foretell
the destruction of Jerusalem.

00:20:50.770 --> 00:20:53.481 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah assured his faithful prophet

00:20:53.481 --> 00:20:58.361 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that the foretold destruction
would “not be late.”

00:20:58.361 --> 00:21:03.241 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He said: “Keep in expectation”

00:21:03.241 --> 00:21:08.204 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—Habakkuk chapter 1
and also chapter 2, verse 3.

00:21:08.204 --> 00:21:12.083 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So don’t you get discouraged by the fact

00:21:12.083 --> 00:21:15.878 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that you have been preaching
for a long time, perhaps decades.

00:21:15.878 --> 00:21:19.340 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In the new world,
all will have reason to reflect

00:21:19.340 --> 00:21:23.261 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
on the fact that all the foretold events

00:21:23.261 --> 00:21:26.222 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
associated with the conclusion
of the system of things

00:21:26.222 --> 00:21:29.809 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
did indeed take place, or have taken place.

00:21:29.809 --> 00:21:33.813 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Meditating on how matters actually turned out

00:21:33.813 --> 00:21:37.108 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
will further strengthen
our confidence in Jehovah

00:21:37.108 --> 00:21:39.902 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and his promises to be fulfilled.

00:21:39.902 --> 00:21:42.572 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We will surely be thankful to God,

00:21:42.572 --> 00:21:46.242 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who ‘has placed times
and seasons in his own jurisdiction.’

00:21:46.242 --> 00:21:48.995 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He exhorted us to live with an awareness

00:21:48.995 --> 00:21:52.290 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that “the end of all things has drawn close.”

00:21:52.290 --> 00:21:55.042 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Bible predicts that political powers

00:21:55.042 --> 00:21:57.670 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
will turn against false religion.

00:21:57.670 --> 00:22:00.756 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We should not assume that much time is needed

00:22:00.756 --> 00:22:03.009 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for the state of this world to develop

00:22:03.009 --> 00:22:05.553 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to the point where political powers,

00:22:05.553 --> 00:22:09.098 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
according to Revelation 17:16,

00:22:09.098 --> 00:22:12.852 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
 turn on the world empire of false religion.

00:22:12.852 --> 00:22:15.897 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It says there in Revelation chapter 17:

00:22:15.897 --> 00:22:20.443 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“And the ten horns that you saw
and the [political] wild beast,

00:22:20.443 --> 00:22:24.280 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“these will hate
the prostitute [false religion]

00:22:24.280 --> 00:22:26.616 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and will make her devastated and naked,

00:22:26.616 --> 00:22:30.953 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and they will eat up her flesh
and completely burn her with fire.”

00:22:32.330 --> 00:22:34.332 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let us bear in mind that God

00:22:34.332 --> 00:22:37.168 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
will “put it into their hearts”
to make that move

00:22:37.168 --> 00:22:40.546 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—and this could happen
swiftly and at any time!

00:22:40.546 --> 00:22:44.175 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The end of this entire
system of things is not far off.

00:22:44.175 --> 00:22:46.761 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
With good reason,
we should heed Jesus’ warning:

00:22:46.761 --> 00:22:49.555 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Pay attention to yourselves that your hearts

00:22:49.555 --> 00:22:52.433 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“never become weighed down with overeating

00:22:52.433 --> 00:22:55.603 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and heavy drinking and anxieties of life,

00:22:55.603 --> 00:22:59.815 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and suddenly that day
be instantly upon you as a snare.”

00:22:59.815 --> 00:23:04.654 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let us be resolved
to serve Jehovah with a sense of urgency,

00:23:04.654 --> 00:23:06.822 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
confident that he “acts in behalf

00:23:06.822 --> 00:23:10.368 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
