00:31:10.389 --> 00:31:13.934 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“To the Governing Body and the Bethel family.

00:31:13.934 --> 00:31:18.939 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Dear Brothers: Upon receiving
our invitation to attend Gilead,

00:31:18.939 --> 00:31:23.110 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“our hearts were filled
with gratitude for Jehovah.

00:31:23.110 --> 00:31:27.030 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Today marks a turning point in our lives,

00:31:27.030 --> 00:31:29.950 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and we would like
to thank the Governing Body

00:31:29.950 --> 00:31:33.162 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“for this opportunity to be taught and molded

00:31:33.162 --> 00:31:36.415 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“by our Grand Instructor, Jehovah God.

00:31:36.415 --> 00:31:41.420 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Your fine example of love
and personal interest has touched us.

00:31:41.420 --> 00:31:46.133 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“In spite of your busy schedule,
you personally came to teach us

00:31:46.133 --> 00:31:49.636 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and help us better understand
‘the mind of Christ.’

00:31:49.636 --> 00:31:52.431 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“As we reflect on how Jehovah

00:31:52.431 --> 00:31:55.350 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“has bestowed upon us
a blessing without measure,

00:31:55.350 --> 00:31:58.061 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“we share the sentiments of the psalmist

00:31:58.061 --> 00:32:02.441 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“in Psalm 116:12, 14, who sang:

00:32:02.441 --> 00:32:07.112 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘With what will I repay Jehovah
for all the good he has done for me?

00:32:07.112 --> 00:32:10.574 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘I will pay my vows to Jehovah

00:32:10.574 --> 00:32:13.368 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“in the presence of all his people.’

00:32:13.368 --> 00:32:16.455 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“We are determined to pay our vows

00:32:16.455 --> 00:32:19.708 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“by using this special training
to serve the interests

00:32:19.708 --> 00:32:23.587 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“of his organization to his praise and honor.

00:32:25.130 --> 00:32:29.510 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“We are very thankful
for the way the Bethel family welcomed us.

00:32:29.510 --> 00:32:33.305 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“In all the complexes,
the hospitality shown was much more

00:32:33.305 --> 00:32:35.933 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“than we could have imagined.

00:32:35.933 --> 00:32:39.561 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“The majority of the class
are Bethelites and,

00:32:39.561 --> 00:32:43.273 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“to a certain degree,
we understand how much work, time,

00:32:43.273 --> 00:32:46.151 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and effort is needed to display hospitality.

00:32:46.151 --> 00:32:48.695 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“You were very attentive to us.

00:32:48.695 --> 00:32:52.950 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“You could read the question marks
on our foreheads when we got lost.

00:32:52.950 --> 00:32:57.704 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“You were patiently standing in line
behind us in the dining room

00:32:57.704 --> 00:33:01.333 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“when we saw
certain foods for the first time.

00:33:01.333 --> 00:33:03.836 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“What can we say?

00:33:03.836 --> 00:33:06.839 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“We feel a part of your family.

00:33:06.839 --> 00:33:10.384 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Additionally, we have seen
such wisdom and love

00:33:10.384 --> 00:33:14.263 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“through the ‘gifts in men’
who have been used as instructors.

00:33:14.263 --> 00:33:19.268 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“You brothers have generously given
of yourselves, in both heart and mind.

00:33:19.268 --> 00:33:22.938 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“By means of your teaching and experiences,

00:33:22.938 --> 00:33:27.609 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“you have helped us
to isolate and apply Bible principles,

00:33:27.609 --> 00:33:32.614 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
”to be people-oriented,
to deal with and see others as Christ did.

00:33:32.614 --> 00:33:36.994 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“It has helped us
cultivate essential qualities

00:33:36.994 --> 00:33:40.998 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“that have changed the fabric
of who we are inside.

00:33:40.998 --> 00:33:43.876 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“You never drew attention to yourselves,

00:33:43.876 --> 00:33:47.004 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“but in all the lessons, we truly appreciate

00:33:47.004 --> 00:33:51.049 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“how you glorified and magnified Jehovah.

00:33:51.049 --> 00:33:54.469 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“As Proverbs 10:22 says:

00:33:54.469 --> 00:33:58.724 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘It is the blessing of Jehovah
that makes one rich.’

00:33:58.724 --> 00:34:02.603 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“We have been enriched
by making new lifelong friends,

00:34:02.603 --> 00:34:05.939 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“but Gilead training does not end here.

00:34:05.939 --> 00:34:09.943 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“As we depart
for our various assignments around the world,

00:34:09.943 --> 00:34:14.031 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“our determination is
to stick ever closer to Jehovah

00:34:14.031 --> 00:34:17.200 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and the work he has assigned to us.

00:34:17.200 --> 00:34:22.205 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Our resolve is to use our training
to stabilize and strengthen our brothers

00:34:22.205 --> 00:34:27.044 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and to bring glory and honor
to our Grand Instructor, Jehovah.

00:34:27.044 --> 00:34:31.340 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“We wish to convey
our gratitude and love to all of you.

00:34:31.340 --> 00:34:35.844 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Your brothers and sisters,
the 147th class of Gilead.”

00:34:53.987 --> 00:34:57.574 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, at the beginning
of this graduation program,

00:34:57.574 --> 00:34:59.993 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I posed a question to all of you,

00:34:59.993 --> 00:35:02.120 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and that question was,

00:35:02.120 --> 00:35:05.999 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How far will you go?

00:35:05.999 --> 00:35:11.004 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, in order to fully serve
our brothers and sisters

00:35:11.004 --> 00:35:16.009 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—to love them, to train them, to help them—

00:35:16.009 --> 00:35:21.014 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
you will have to make
major sacrifices in your life.

00:35:21.014 --> 00:35:23.475 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Some of you are making them right now

00:35:23.475 --> 00:35:28.105 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in order to accept some
of the assignments that you received today.

00:35:28.105 --> 00:35:30.899 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But I wanted to share
with you a Bible account

00:35:30.899 --> 00:35:33.568 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that I’d like for you
to try to keep in your minds,

00:35:33.568 --> 00:35:36.321 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
because you never know
when the phone is going to ring

00:35:36.321 --> 00:35:38.865 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or that e-mail is going to come.

00:35:38.865 --> 00:35:43.328 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s go to 2 Chronicles chapter 25,

00:35:45.414 --> 00:35:48.834 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and here we read about King Amaziah.

00:35:48.834 --> 00:35:51.753 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s very interesting
what the Bible says here.

00:35:51.753 --> 00:35:56.758 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, it mentions in verse 6
of 2 Chronicles chapter 25

00:35:56.758 --> 00:35:59.803 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that Amaziah hired from Israel

00:35:59.803 --> 00:36:04.808 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
100,000 mighty warriors
for 100 silver talents.

00:36:04.808 --> 00:36:08.061 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, I didn’t do all the math.

00:36:08.061 --> 00:36:10.063 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Sorry, Brother Splane.

00:36:10.063 --> 00:36:14.443 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But I understand that this is well,

00:36:14.443 --> 00:36:18.405 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
well over $1,000,000 in today’s money.

00:36:18.405 --> 00:36:22.701 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So this is a very,
very large sum that Amaziah had paid,

00:36:23.952 --> 00:36:27.497 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but after he had done so, look at verse 7:

00:36:27.497 --> 00:36:30.917 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“But a man of the true God
came to him, saying:

00:36:30.917 --> 00:36:35.797 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘O king, do not let
the army of Israel go with you,

00:36:35.797 --> 00:36:40.802 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘for Jehovah is not with Israel,
not with any of the Ephraimites.

00:36:40.802 --> 00:36:45.807 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘But go by yourself, . . .
and be courageous in battle.

00:36:45.807 --> 00:36:50.812 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘Otherwise, the true God could cause you
to stumble before an enemy,

00:36:50.812 --> 00:36:55.817 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for God has the power
to help and to cause stumbling.’”

00:36:55.817 --> 00:37:00.739 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, how did Amaziah react to that counsel?

00:37:00.739 --> 00:37:04.159 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You see right away in verse 9:

00:37:04.159 --> 00:37:07.162 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Amaziah said to the man of the true God:

00:37:07.162 --> 00:37:11.875 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘But what about the 100 talents
that I have given to the troops of Israel?’”

00:37:11.875 --> 00:37:16.546 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Right?
He had already paid the money.

00:37:16.546 --> 00:37:21.384 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, now, how could we apply
that principle to you?

00:37:21.384 --> 00:37:26.389 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, many of you
may have made major sacrifices already

00:37:26.389 --> 00:37:28.975 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in your career of full-time service.

00:37:28.975 --> 00:37:31.394 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Maybe you’ve had to learn a new language.

00:37:31.394 --> 00:37:34.356 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Maybe you’ve made an investment of time

00:37:34.356 --> 00:37:38.777 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in your department at Bethel
or in your field assignment,

00:37:38.777 --> 00:37:41.780 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and now you’re being asked
to do something different

00:37:41.780 --> 00:37:44.199 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—perhaps learn a whole new language

00:37:44.199 --> 00:37:49.204 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or go from the field to Bethel
or from Bethel to the field.

00:37:49.204 --> 00:37:52.374 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, will you feel like Amaziah?

00:37:52.374 --> 00:37:56.503 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Will you say, ‘What about those 100 talents

00:37:56.503 --> 00:37:58.797 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that I’ve already paid?’

00:37:58.797 --> 00:38:03.635 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, here’s the answer
that I’d like for you to keep in your mind.

00:38:03.635 --> 00:38:06.638 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The man of the true God, in verse 9,

00:38:06.638 --> 00:38:11.017 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
answered Amaziah, and this is what he said:

00:38:11.017 --> 00:38:16.022 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Jehovah has the means
to give you much more than that.”

00:38:16.022 --> 00:38:21.027 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And that’s the thought
you want to treasure in your mind and heart.

00:38:21.027 --> 00:38:26.032 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When you’re asked to take up
some new challenge, some new assignment

00:38:26.032 --> 00:38:29.077 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—and it may mean walking away 

00:38:29.077 --> 00:38:32.831 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from a large investment
that you have already made—

00:38:32.831 --> 00:38:35.792 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
remember: Jehovah has the power

00:38:35.792 --> 00:38:39.838 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to give you much more than that.

00:38:39.838 --> 00:38:42.465 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, with those thoughts in mind,

00:38:42.465 --> 00:38:47.470 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
may you go with all of our love,
with our deep respect,

00:38:47.470 --> 00:38:50.891 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and with the blessing
of our wonderful,

00:38:50.891 --> 00:38:53.602 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
our amazing God, Jehovah.

